name: Test -> output of relay (ambient sensor module),
description: Test the voltage on both sides of the relay output terminals during both 'on' and 'off' lamp states, to confirm whether the relay is switching as expected or if instability is due to the relay output fluctuations., outcome='Voltage measurements indicate nearly identical readings at voltage_p and voltage_n terminals on the control relay, which suggests extremely low voltage across the relay output. Both the main lamp and internal indicator lamp show approximately 11 V at their positive terminals and near zero at negative, consistent with expected polarity (no polarity inversion detected). The simulation notes instability or oscillation in the circuit operation.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module light sensor circuit,
description: Test the stability and output of the light sensor circuit in the ambient sensor module, including measuring its continuous voltage output (and any fluctuations or noise), to verify if the sensor control signal is contributing to relay oscillation or instability., outcome='The measured voltages indicate a large potential difference across the ambient light sensor (5.91 V), as well as across the sensor bias resistor (approx. 5.91 V), and the system is in an unstable or oscillating state according to the simulation. No polarity inversions were detected in your measurements of input/output cables. The instability in the light sensor circuit may be contributing to relay oscillation or general module instability.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=205.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
